The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Essar BPO unit takes over PeopleSupport
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Essar BPO unit takes over PeopleSupport
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                                          
	Mumbai, Aug. 4: Essar Groups Aegis BPO is taking over PeopleSupport Inc, a leading offshore BPO provider, and will merge it with its subsidiary Essar Services (Mauritius) in a cash transaction valued at around $250 million.         
	Under the agreement, Aegis BPO will pay $12.25 per share to PeopleSupport stockholders through Essar Services (Mauritius), a premium of approximately 29 per cent over PeopleSupports closing share price on August 1, 2008, the last trading day prior to todays announcement.        
	Although headquartered in Los Angeles, California, a majority of PeopleSupports services are carried out in the Philippines, where it is one of the largest outsourcing companies employing around 8,000 personnel.        
	The company serves clients in the sectors of travel, consumer, financial services, healthcare, insurance, technology, telecommunications, entertainment and education.        
	After the merger, Aegis BPO will have a global footprint with operations in India, the Philippines, the US and Costa Rica.        
	With around 4,000 employees in the US and more than 25,000 employees in several offshore locations, Aegis BPO is well positioned to provide onshore, nearshore and offshore BPO services or a combination of customised solutions.         
	Lance Rosenzweig, PeopleSupport CEO and chairman, said, PeopleSupport has pioneered the development of offshore BPO in the Philippines and Costa Rica and we are excited to become part of a global outsourcing leader.         
	Aparup Sengupta, global CEO and managing director of Aegis BPO, said, This is a truly outstanding combination that extends Aegis capabilities across multiple geographies and domains that is one of the key strategies of becoming a global outsourcing leader.                                                                                                                                      
